rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence, preferably
    from multiple sources or systems, to ensure architectural stability.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must participate in a shared Knowledge Workspace and avoid creating
    duplicate workspace-level governance structures.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be recorded as structured decision records
    (ADR) before being reflected in AEM or other artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All decisions must be expressed using a structured YAML decision schema
    rather than unstructured narrative text to enable machine processing.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures consistent interpretation between pattern maturity and decision
    lifecycle, preventing the conflation of knowledge evolution and governance validation.
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be merged or consolidated across different architectural
    layers to maintain separation between governance, execution, and contracts.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of any architecture item must be derived from its decision
    status; items not marked 'accepted' cannot be marked as DONE.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the semantic contract for language in architecture artifacts, distinguishing
    between intent and state, and defining specific lifecycle terminology.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: 'Candidate signals are eligible for pattern promotion only if they satisfy
    mandatory criteria: recurrence, system impact, reusability, and stability.'
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be created as supporting by default and never directly
    as core to ensure they are validated through evidence before becoming foundational.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) must remain consistent with and never
    contradict Architecture Decision Records (ADR).
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-architecture-work-authority
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Work is the authoritative source of planning state; all generated
    artifacts must derive their status from this registry.
  title: Rule Architecture Work Authority
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All runtime-native workflows must conform to the CAS Workflow Execution
    Model, maintaining strict separation between orchestration, reasoning, and knowledge
    access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated only in ADRs; all other
    representations, including pattern metadata and AEM, must be derived from them.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-generated-artifacts-not-authoritative
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Generated governance artifacts like AEM and AID summarize authoritative
    sources but must not become the authoritative source themselves.
  title: Rule Generated Artifacts Not Authoritative
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: 'Defines the precedence model for resolving conflicts: Global Rules take
    absolute precedence over Project Rules, which take precedence over Prompt Rules.'
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be proposed by the system and explicitly
    accepted, rejected, or deferred by a human architect.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns must represent foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific strategies or replaceable implementations.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All heuristic-derived patterns must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure traceability and grounding in observed behavior.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
summary:
  global_rules: 19
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 19
